<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FFA7FFDB38860D0B45BBBD77" author="Bentham, G." box="[477,661,1597,1624]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" pagination="335 - 375" refId="ref41649" refString="Bentham, G. (1875) Revision of the suborder Mimoseae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 30 (3): 335 - 375. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1875. tb 00005. x" type="journal article" year="1875">Bentham (1875)</bibRefCitation>
refers to 
<specimenCount id="B5F625DBFFA7FFDB3A5F0D0844B7BD77" box="[772,921,1598,1624]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
for 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA7FFDB3A900D084378BD78" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1875" box="[971,1110,1597,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obovatum">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3A900D084378BD78" box="[971,1110,1597,1624]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">S. obovatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicating only the collection sites, which corresponds to 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB38E40D574573BD53" box="[447,605,1633,1660]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Burchell 8343</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3BC80D5745D8BD54" box="[659,758,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Pohl s.n.</emphasis>
(
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3A5E0D574467BD53" box="[773,841,1633,1660]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Goiás</collectingRegion>
) and 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3AD30D574329BD54" box="[904,1031,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Weddel s.n.</emphasis>
(
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3D4D0D544385BD53" box="[1046,1195,1634,1660]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
) in his following work (
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FFA7FFDB39CB0DB34617BD8F" author="Bentham, G." box="[144,313,1669,1696]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" pagination="257 - 502" refId="ref41697" refString="Bentham, G. (1876) Leguminosae II et III. Mimoseae. In: Martius, C. F. P. (Ed.) Flora brasiliensis. v. 15, pars 2. Lipsiae apud Frid. Fleishcer in Comm., Monachii, pp. 257 - 502." type="book chapter" year="1876">Bentham 1876</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB380F0DB346DCBD8F" box="[340,498,1669,1696]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Burchell 8343</emphasis>
deposited in K is here selected as 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FFA7FFDB3A2F0DB344F0BDB0" box="[884,990,1669,1695]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA7FFDB39E60D9F43DDBDC8" blockId="41.[136,1452,1561,2092]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">
Although the protologues of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA7FFDB38A60D9C455ABDEC" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1841" box="[509,628,1705,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB38A60D9C455ABDEC" box="[509,628,1705,1732]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">S. discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA7FFDB3BF30D9C4472BDEC" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1837" box="[680,860,1705,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolium">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3BF30D9C4472BDEC" box="[680,860,1705,1732]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">S. rotundifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fo. 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3ADD0D9C44E5BDEC" box="[902,971,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">retusa</emphasis>
cited only one collection as their 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FFA7FFDB3C650D9C4252BDEB" box="[1342,1404,1706,1732]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">types</typeStatus>
, our searches revealed several duplicates of each of them, requiring the lectotypifications performed here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA7FFD839E60DC743A4BA66" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="269" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA7FFD839E60DC74360BA0A" blockId="41.[136,1452,1561,2092]" lastBlockId="42.[136,1451,158,545]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="269" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB39E60DC746C3BC24" bold="true" box="[189,493,1777,1804]" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—Among the Central Brazilian species of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA7FFDB3A8E0DC743B8BC24" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1837" box="[981,1174,1777,1803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3A8E0DC743B8BC24" box="[981,1174,1777,1803]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Stryphnodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA7FFDB3DFD0DC44273BC24" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1837" box="[1190,1373,1777,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="41" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolium">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3DFD0DC44273BC24" box="[1190,1373,1777,1804]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">S. rotundifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the widest geographical distribution, mostly occurring in drier areas with high luminosity and generally on sandy soils. It grows predominantly in areas of cerrado, campo cerrado, campo limpo and cerradão in Central-Western and Southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA7FFDB38090C6B46B8BC58" box="[338,406,1885,1911]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB38FC0C684510BC57" box="[423,574,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3B100C68441DBC58" box="[587,819,1885,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3A1B0C6B44AABC58" box="[832,900,1885,1911]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3ACB0C6B44D1BC58" box="[912,1023,1885,1911]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3D570C6843ACBC58" box="[1036,1154,1885,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3DD50C6B4208BC58" box="[1166,1318,1885,1911]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3C040C684285BC57" box="[1375,1451,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Paraná</collectingRegion>
states), and adjacent areas of 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA7FFDB38830CB4456EBCB3" box="[472,576,1922,1948]" name="Paraguay" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA7FFDB3B210CB745FEBCB4" box="[634,720,1921,1947]" name="Bolivia" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. It is also observed in the transition region between the Cerrado and Caatinga domains, from the northernmost part of Minas Gerais towards Northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA7FFDB3DC90C9343F8BC90" box="[1170,1238,1957,1983]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3DBC0C934273BC90" box="[1255,1373,1957,1983]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB3C300C934289BC90" box="[1387,1447,1957,1983]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Piauí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB39D30CFC47E7BCCB" box="[136,201,1994,2020]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Ceará</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA7FFDB38580CFF466ABCCC" box="[259,324,1993,2019]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Bahia</collectingRegion>
states), where the populations are in most cases associated with high altitude areas, such as 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB3C390CFC4285BCCB" box="[1378,1451,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Serras</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91843240FFA7FFDB39E20CDB4605B328" box="[185,299,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Chapadas</emphasis>
. Specimens were also collected in campinaranas of Northern 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA7FFDB3AB10CDB4300B328" box="[1002,1070,2029,2055]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Amazonas and Pará states). The only register of the species in Southern 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA7FFDB3B070327458EB304" box="[604,672,2065,2091]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="268">Brazil</collectingCountry>
refers to a cultivated tree grown from seeds collected in “north of 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FFA4FFD839D30BA847FFBB97" box="[136,209,158,184]" name="Brazil" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Brazil</collectingCountry>
”, this meaning, according to local Southern concept, any state north of 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83D5E0BA843BFBB96" box="[1029,1169,158,185]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Paraná state</collectingRegion>
. Likewise, all herbarium records of this species from the east coast of Africa are also explicitly indicated as being cultivated. The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA4FFD839FC0BD14673BA2F" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1837" box="[167,349,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolium">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839FC0BD14673BA2F" box="[167,349,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">S. rotundifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD838D90BD0450BBA2F" box="[386,549,230,256]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD83B6E0BD045F4BA2F" box="[565,730,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Glaziou 10611</emphasis>
at K) is unlikely, most probably being a mislabeling of samples collected in São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FFA4FFD83B180A3C45F2BA0B" box="[579,732,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, as indicated in its duplicate at P.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA4FFD839E60A1843A4BA66" blockId="42.[136,1451,158,545]" box="[189,1162,302,329]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839E60A184649BA67" bold="true" box="[189,359,302,328]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Conservation:</emphasis>
—Least Concern (LC) [AOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FFA4FFD83BE60A184468BA67" box="[701,838,302,328]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" unit="km" value="600.0">600.000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFFA4FFD83A1E0A184463BA13" attach="left" box="[837,845,302,316]" fontSize="6" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">2</superScript>
, EOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FFA4FFD83AFF0A18435FBA67" box="[932,1137,302,329]" metricMagnitude="9" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.953431253" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" unit="km" value="4953431.253">4,953,431.253 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFFA4FFD83D2A0A184357BA13" attach="left" box="[1137,1145,302,316]" fontSize="6" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">2</superScript>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA4FFD839E60A6446C8BABE" pageId="42" pageNumber="269" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA4FFD839E60A6446C8BABE" blockId="42.[136,1451,158,545]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA4FFD839E60A64466DBA43" bold="true" box="[189,323,338,364]" pageId="42" pageNumber="269">Phenology:</emphasis>
—This taxon was collected with flowers and fruits throughout the year, except in June and August (flowers) and February (fruits).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
